This is homework 3 (including extra credit) for Interative Computer Graphics, by Shangqi Wu.

This program is developed with the virtual machine provided by this course. 

To compile this program, please use the makefile and type "make" in command line. Executable file will be named "hw3". Command "make clean" can remove the executable file.

To run this program, please type "./hw3" in command line. This program sucessfully fulfills all requirements in the homework instructions. It creates a main window with squares described, a subwindow with ellipse, and another window containing a triangle and a circle. You can choose to start and stop animation, also change colors, using menus and keyboards. To test these functions, please just do the same as homework description. 

Also, extra credit part is implemented, when you left click your mouse, a new breathing circle with random color is created. 
